{"format": "tiptap/v1", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Text embedding models convert strings into fixed-length vectors that capture semantic meaning. The model family you choose — sparse lexical, dense bi-encoder, or cross-encoder — determines the accuracy-speed tradeoff and how you build your index. Understanding the families helps you pick the right tool for each stage of a retrieval pipeline."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Three text embedding families: sparse (TF-IDF/BM25), dense bi-encoder, and cross-encoder reranker — with trade-offs and best-use cases."}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sparse Embeddings (Lexical)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sparse models produce vocabulary-sized vectors where most values are zero. The non-zero entries correspond to words present in the text. BM25 is the canonical example — fast, no training required, and excellent for exact keyword matching."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from rank_bm25 import BM25Okapi\n\ndocs = [\n    \"cats are small carnivores that hunt rodents\",\n    \"dogs are loyal companions and working animals\",\n    \"Python is a high-level programming language\",\n]\ntokenized = [d.split() for d in docs]\nbm25 = BM25Okapi(tokenized)\n\nscores = bm25.get_scores(\"feline hunting\".split())\nprint(scores)   # [2.18, 0.0, 0.0]  — only doc 0 has any matching tokens\n\nscores = bm25.get_scores(\"cat hunting rodent\".split())\nprint(scores)   # [4.31, 0.0, 0.0]  — higher: 3 matching tokens\n\n# BM25 completely misses semantic near-matches\nscores = bm25.get_scores(\"feline animals\".split())\nprint(scores)   # [0.0, 0.0, 0.0]  — no lexical overlap with any doc"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dense Bi-Encoder Embeddings"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dense models map text to a compact fixed-length vector (128–4096 dimensions). All values are non-zero — the full semantic meaning is distributed across every dimension. Similarity is computed by cosine or dot product, which is fast enough to search millions of vectors in milliseconds."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer\nimport numpy as np\n\nmodel = SentenceTransformer(\"all-MiniLM-L6-v2\")\n\ndocs = [\n    \"cats are small carnivores that hunt rodents\",\n    \"dogs are loyal companions and working animals\",\n    \"Python is a high-level programming language\",\n]\nquery = \"feline animals\"\n\ndoc_vecs = model.encode(docs, normalize_embeddings=True)\nq_vec = model.encode([query], normalize_embeddings=True)\n\nscores = (q_vec @ doc_vecs.T)[0]\nfor doc, score in zip(docs, scores):\n    print(f\"{score:.3f}  {doc}\")\n# 0.742  cats are small carnivores that hunt rodents\n# 0.547  dogs are loyal companions and working animals  ← semantic match\n# 0.157  Python is a high-level programming language"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The dense model correctly identifies both the cat and dog documents as animal-related, even though \"feline\" appears in neither. The sparse BM25 scored them all at 0."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Symmetric vs. Asymmetric Models"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Some bi-encoders are symmetric: queries and documents use the same model with no special treatment. Others are asymmetric: queries and documents go through different processing — typically a prefix or separate encoder — because short queries and long passages occupy different regions of the embedding space."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer\n\n# Symmetric — same model, no prefix\nsym_model = SentenceTransformer(\"all-MiniLM-L6-v2\")\ndoc_vecs = sym_model.encode(docs, normalize_embeddings=True)\nq_vec = sym_model.encode([\"feline animals\"], normalize_embeddings=True)\n\n# Asymmetric with e5 — requires 'query: ' / 'passage: ' prefixes\ne5 = SentenceTransformer(\"intfloat/multilingual-e5-large\")\ndoc_vecs_e5 = e5.encode(\n    [f\"passage: {d}\" for d in docs],\n    normalize_embeddings=True,\n)\nq_vec_e5 = e5.encode(\n    [\"query: feline animals\"],  # ← prefix required\n    normalize_embeddings=True,\n)\n\n# Asymmetric with bge via prompt_name\nbge = SentenceTransformer(\"BAAI/bge-m3\")\ndoc_vecs_bge = bge.encode(docs, normalize_embeddings=True)       # no prefix for docs\nq_vec_bge = bge.encode(\n    [\"feline animals\"],\n    prompt_name=\"query\",       # applies model-specific query prefix\n    normalize_embeddings=True,\n)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-Encoders for Reranking"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A cross-encoder takes a (query, document) pair as a single concatenated input and outputs a single relevance score. This joint encoding lets the model attend across both texts simultaneously, producing much more accurate relevance judgements than a bi-encoder — but at the cost of being impossible to pre-compute: you must run the model separately for every (query, document) pair at query time."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from sentence_transformers import CrossEncoder\n\nreranker = CrossEncoder(\"cross-encoder/ms-marco-MiniLM-L-6-v2\")\n\nquery = \"feline animals\"\n\n# Cross-encoder takes (query, doc) pairs — no separate encode step\npairs = [(query, doc) for doc in docs]\nscores = reranker.predict(pairs)   # shape (3,)\nprint(scores)\n# e.g. [ 5.32, 2.18, -3.87]\n# Higher = more relevant. Calibration varies by model — compare relative, not absolute.\n\n# In practice: bi-encoder retrieves top-100, cross-encoder reranks them\n# Cross-encoder is ~100x slower per-doc than bi-encoder, but only runs on 100 docs\nranked = sorted(zip(docs, scores), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\nfor doc, score in ranked:\n    print(f\"{score:.2f}  {doc}\")"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Choosing a Model"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Task"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Recommended approach"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Exact keyword / product code search"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "BM25 (sparse)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Semantic search / RAG retrieval"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dense bi-encoder (bge-m3 or nomic)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best of keyword + semantic"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hybrid: BM25 + bi-encoder with RRF"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "High-precision top-5 results"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bi-encoder retrieve → cross-encoder rerank"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Clustering, classification, deduplication"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dense bi-encoder (symmetric)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Context Window Limits"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Every embedding model has a maximum token input length. Text beyond that limit is truncated silently — the tail of a long document is ignored."}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Max tokens"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "all-MiniLM-L6-v2"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "256"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "BAAI/bge-m3"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "8192"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "nomic-embed-text-v1.5"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "8192"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "text-embedding-3-small"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "8191"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For RAG pipelines, chunk documents to comfortably fit within the model's window (e.g. 512 tokens for a 512-limit model, leaving room for overlap). For models with 8k+ context, you can embed whole sections or short documents without chunking."}]}]}}